<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 13 at 6:42PM EST  by NWS Albany</headline>
<description>...SNOW SHOWERS WITH MODERATE TO HEAVY SNOW WILL AFFECT PARTS OF
SOUTHERN BERKSHIRE...EASTERN COLUMBIA...AND WESTERN COLUMBIA
COUNTIES...
HAZARDS...Snow showers accompanied by winds of up to 30 MPH which
can rapidly reduce visibility to less than one mile.
LOCATION AND MOVEMENT...At 640 PM EST, snow showers were near
Austerlitz, or near Chatham moving southeast at 35 MPH.
THESE SNOW SHOWERS WILL BE NEAR...Great Barrington and Housatonic
around 650 PM EST.
SAFETY INFO...
Conditions can deteriorate rapidly in winter weather situations. Be
prepared for snow or ice covered roads. Slow down and allow extra
time to reach your destination.
&amp;&amp;</description>
